FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778576786
OL,3,CTice declines to condemn councillor's
OL,4,C'Nigerians should fill pot holes'
OL,5,Cremark
OL,7,F"Should melt them all down and fill in
OL,8,Fthe pot holes!!" he wrote in a later-
OL,9,Fdeleted post, according to campaign
OL,10,Fgroup Hope Not Hate.
OL,12,FReform deputy leader Richard Tice on
OL,13,FSunday refused to directly criticise
OL,14,FMr Gibbins as he accused the media of
OL,15,F"smearing" Nigel Farage's party.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@PO]wD@AOUwD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778576786
OL,3,CTice declines to condemn councillor's
OL,4,C'Nigerians should fill pot holes'
OL,5,Cremark
OL,7,FAsked whether he was happy for someone
OL,8,Fwith those views to represent the
OL,9,Fparty, Mr Tice told the BBC's Sunday
OL,10,FWith Laura Kuenssberg programme: "This
OL,11,Fweekend we are celebrating our
OL,12,Fincredible successes.
OL,14,F"Like any party, we have internal
OL,15,Fparty processes to look where people
OL,16,Fhave said or done the wrong thing."
OL,18,FHe continued: "I condemn everything
OL,19,Fthat is wrong and inappropriate.
OL,26,@rD@bOUvD@AOUxD@cO]zD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778576786
OL,3,CTice declines to condemn councillor's
OL,4,C'Nigerians should fill pot holes'
OL,5,Cremark
OL,7,F"Voters have heard all of this
OL,8,Fsmearing and this sneering against all
OL,9,Fof us, and they have voted for more
OL,10,FReform."
OL,12,FEducation Secretary Bridget Phillipson
OL,13,Fsaid the case was an example of "the
OL,14,Fkind of racism and division" Reform
OL,15,Fbrought to politics, in an interview
OL,16,Fon the same programme.
OL,18,FA Labour Party spokesperson said:
OL,19,F"It's utterly grotesque that Reform
OL,20,Fcan't even call out clear racism.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@HO]uD@aOUvD@\O]{D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778576786
OL,3,CTice declines to condemn councillor's
OL,4,C'Nigerians should fill pot holes'
OL,5,Cremark
OL,7,F"It speaks volumes that Richard Tice
OL,8,Ftried to brush off these comments.
OL,10,F"And it speaks volumes that Nigel
OL,11,FFarage refused to sack him as a
OL,12,Fcandidate and is now happy to have him
OL,13,Frepresent Reform as a councillor.
OL,14,FThey're both a disgrace.
OL,16,F"Labour is the only party that will
OL,17,Fstand up to the division of Reform."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@AOUxD@AOUyD@dO]
